"title": "5197: walking",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5197: walking",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The action of travelling on foot at a normal pace. The image of walking with God is used in Scripture to represent the behaviour of believers in their relationship with God.</p>\n<h2>The physical activity of walking</h2>\n<h3>For travel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:17\">GEN 13:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:7\">DEU 6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:10\">JDG 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:7\">1KI 18:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:3\">AMO 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:18\">MAT 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:17\">LUK 24:17</a></p>\n<h3>As a miracle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:5\">MAT 11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:25-Matt14:26\">MAT 14:25–14:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:6-Acts3:8\">ACT 3:6–3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:10\">ACT 14:10</a></p>\n<h3>God walking</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:12\">LEV 26:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8\">GEN 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Walking used figuratively of human behaviour</h2>\n<h3>Walking in sin and darkness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:26\">1KI 15:26</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:12-Prov2:13\">PRO 2:12–2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1\">PSA 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps82:5\">PSA 82:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:12-Prov2:13\">PRO 2:12–2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:6\">1JN 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Sometimes darkness represents depressing circumstances</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:2\">LAM 3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:4\">PSA 23:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:2\">ISA 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:9\">ISA 59:9</a></p>\n<h3>Walking with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:22-Gen5:24\">GEN 5:22–5:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:1\">GEN 17:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:4\">REV 3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:9\">GEN 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:6\">DEU 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:12\">DEU 10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:3-1Kgs2:4\">1KI 2:3–2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:3\">ISA 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:23\">JER 7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:5\">MIC 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:8\">MIC 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:7\">ZEC 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:6\">MAL 2:6</a></p>\n<h3>Walking in the truth or in the light</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:33\">DEU 5:33</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps15:2\">PSA 15:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps26:2-Ps26:3\">PSA 26:2–26:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:13\">PSA 56:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:11\">PSA 86:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:15\">PSA 89:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:12\">PRO 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:5\">ISA 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:4-2John1:6\">2JN 1:4–1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3John1:3-3John1:4\">3JN 1:3–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:24\">REV 21:24</a></p>\n<h3>Walking as a way of living or behaving</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:1-Eph2:2\">EPH 2:1–2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1\">ROM 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:7\">2CO 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:1\">EPH 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:2\">EPH 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:10\">COL 1:10</a></p>",
